{
  "Profit & Loss Analysis": "利润和损失分析",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "这个课程涵盖了分析和总结数据集的中心的基本测量方法。 您将学会如何计算和应用平均值、 中位数和模式, 并了解何时最合适 。",
  "What is 'revenue' in the context of a profit and loss statement?": "利润和损失说明中的“收入”是什么?",
  "Revenue is the total income generated from the sale of goods or services before any costs or expenses are subtracted. It is the starting point of the income statement.": "收入是指在扣除任何成本或费用之前销售货物或服务所得的总收入,是损益表的起点。",
  "What is 'depreciation' in accounting?": "会计中什么是“折旧”?",
  "Depreciation is an accounting method that systematically spreads the cost of a tangible long-term asset (like machinery or vehicles) over its estimated useful life, reducing reported profit without an actual outflow of cash.": "折旧是一种会计方法,在有形长期资产(如机械或车辆)的估计使用寿命期间,系统地将成本(如机械或车辆)摊分,减少所报告的利润,而不实际现金流出。",
  "What is the 'bottom line' on an income statement?": "收入表上的“底线”是什么?",
  "Net income is called the 'bottom line' because it literally appears as the last line on the income statement, representing the final profit or loss after all revenues and expenses are accounted for.": "净收入称为“底线”,因为它实际上是收入报表最后一行,是所有收入和支出入账后的最后损益。",
  "A clothing store has $350,000 in annual revenue, COGS of $140,000, and operating expenses of $120,000. What is the store's net profit before taxes?": "服装店的年收入为350 000美元,140 000美元,业务开支为120 000美元。 商店税前的净利润是多少?",
  "Gross profit = $350,000 - $140,000 = $210,000. Net profit before taxes = $210,000 - $120,000 = $90,000.": "毛利润=350 000美元 - 140 000美元 = 210 000美元 税前净利润= 210 000美元 - 120 000美元 = 90 000美元。",
  "A tech company has $800,000 in revenue and a 70% gross margin. If operating expenses are $300,000, what is the net income before taxes?": "一个技术公司有80万美元的收入和70%的毛差。 如果业务开支是30万美元,那么税前的净收入是多少?",
  "Gross profit = $800,000 x 0.70 = $560,000. Net income before taxes = $560,000 - $300,000 = $260,000.": "毛利润=800 000美元x0.70美元=560 000美元,税前净收入=560 000美元-300 000美元=260 000美元。",
  "A restaurant earns $500,000 in revenue. COGS is $175,000 and operating expenses total $225,000. What is the restaurant's net profit margin?": "一家餐馆的收入为50万美元,COGS为175,000美元,营业费用共计225,000美元,餐厅的净利润率是多少?",
  "Gross profit = $500,000 - $175,000 = $325,000. Net profit = $325,000 - $225,000 = $100,000. Net profit margin = $100,000 / $500,000 = 20%.": "总利润=500 000美元 - 175 000美元 = 325 000美元 净利润= 325 000美元 - 225 000美元 = 100 000美元 净利润率= 100 000美元 / 500 000美元 = 20% 。",
  "A SaaS company has monthly revenue of $120,000, COGS of $18,000, and operating expenses of $85,000. What is its gross margin percentage and net profit?": "SaaS公司的月收入为120 000美元,COGS为18 000美元,业务开支为85 000美元。 其总利润率和净利润是多少?",
  "Gross profit = $120,000 - $18,000 = $102,000. Gross margin = $102,000 / $120,000 = 85%. Net profit = $102,000 - $85,000 = $17,000.": "总利润=120 000美元 - 18 000美元 = 102 000美元 总利润 = 102 000美元 / 120 000美元 = 85% 净利润 = 102 000美元 - 85 000美元 = 17 000美元。",
  "A coffee shop has $8,000/month fixed costs. Each drink has a selling price of $5 and a variable cost of $1.50. The shop currently sells 3,000 drinks per month. What is its monthly profit and margin of safety in units?": "咖啡店每月有8 000美元的固定费用,每杯饮料的销售价为5美元,可变价格为1.50美元,该店目前每月销售3 000杯。",
  "CM per drink = $5.00 - $1.50 = $3.50. Total CM = 3,000 x $3.50 = $10,500. Profit = $10,500 - $8,000 = $2,500. BEP = $8,000 / $3.50 ≈ 2,286 units. Margin of safety = 3,000 - 2,286 = about 714 units above break-even.": "每杯饮料CM=5.00美元-1.50美元=3.50美元;CM=3,000美元x3.50美元=10,500美元;利润=10,500美元-8,000美元=2,500美元;BEP=8,000美元/3.50美元=2,286美元;安全边缘=3,000美元-2,286美元=约714单位。",
  "A company buys equipment for $60,000 with a 5-year useful life and no salvage value (straight-line depreciation). If annual revenue is $200,000, COGS is $90,000, and other operating expenses total $80,000, what is the annual net profit before taxes?": "一家公司以60,000美元的价格购买设备,其使用寿命为5年,没有残值(直线折旧 ) 。 如果年收入为200,000美元,COGS为90,000美元,其他业务开支为80,000美元,税前年度净利润是多少?",
  "Annual depreciation = $60,000 / 5 = $12,000. Gross profit = $200,000 - $90,000 = $110,000. Total operating expenses = $80,000 + $12,000 = $92,000. Net profit before taxes = $110,000 - $92,000 = $18,000.": "每年折旧 = 60 000 / 5 = 12 000美元 毛利润 = 200 000 - 90 000 = 110 000美元 业务费用总额 = 80 000 + 12 000 = 92 000美元 税前净利润 = 110 000 - 92 000 = 18 000美元。",
  "What does 'operating leverage' refer to?": "“业务杠杆”指的是什么?",
  "Operating leverage describes how a company's cost structure (specifically its mix of fixed vs. variable costs) affects profitability. High operating leverage means small revenue changes lead to large profit swings.": "业务杠杆说明公司的成本结构(特别是固定成本和可变成本的组合)如何影响利润率,高业务杠杆意味着收入的微小变化导致大额利润波动。",
  "A business with high operating leverage has $200,000 in fixed costs and low variable costs (10% of revenue). If revenue increases from $500,000 to $600,000, by how much does profit increase?": "一个拥有高经营杠杆的企业在固定成本和低可变成本方面拥有20万美元(收入的10%),如果收入从50万美元增加到60万美元,利润增加多少?",
  "At $500K revenue: Variable costs = $50K, Fixed costs = $200K, Profit = $500K - $50K - $200K = $250K. At $600K revenue: Variable costs = $60K, Fixed costs = $200K, Profit = $600K - $60K - $200K = $340K. Profit increase = $340K - $250K = $90K. A 20% revenue increase caused a 36% profit increase, demonstrating high operating leverage.": "按500K收入计算:可变费用=50K美元;固定费用=200K美元;利润=500K美元;利润=500K美元-50K美元-200K美元=250K美元;按600K收入计算:可变费用=60K美元;固定费用=200K美元;利润=600K美元-60K美元-200K美元=340K美元;利润增加额=340K美元-250K美元=90K美元;收入增加20%导致利润增加36%,表明业务杠杆作用很大。"
}